🔥 ASSIGNMENT 5 — LAUNCH A VIRTUAL MACHINE USING AWS EC2
COMPLETE FINAL STEP-BY-STEP PRACTICAL SHEET
This is the clean practical execution flow for creating and connecting to an AWS EC2 Virtual Machine.

🎯 AIM
To create and launch a Virtual Machine (EC2 Instance) using AWS Cloud.

🧠 REQUIREMENTS
✅ AWS account ✅ Internet connection ✅ Terminal (Mac/Linux) ✅ SSH enabled

🌐 COMPLETE FLOW
Login AWS
↓
Open EC2 Dashboard
↓
Launch Instance
↓
Choose Ubuntu AMI
↓
Create Key Pair
↓
Configure Security Group
↓
Launch Instance
↓
Connect using SSH
↓
Run Linux commands

✅ STEP 1 — LOGIN TO AWS
Open:
AWS Console
Login using AWS credentials.

✅ STEP 2 — OPEN EC2 DASHBOARD
In AWS search bar type:
EC2
Click:
EC2

🎯 WHAT IS EC2?
EC2 = Elastic Compute Cloud
Used to: ✅ create virtual machines in cloud.

✅ STEP 3 — CLICK “LAUNCH INSTANCE”
Click:
Launch Instance

🎯 WHAT IS INSTANCE?
Instance = virtual machine.

✅ STEP 4 — GIVE INSTANCE NAME
Example:
VM1
OR
CloudVM

✅ STEP 5 — CHOOSE AMAZON MACHINE IMAGE (AMI)
🔥 VERY IMPORTANT
AMI = Amazon Machine Image
Used to select: ✅ Operating System

SELECT:
Ubuntu Server
Choose: ✅ Free Tier Eligible

🎯 WHAT HAPPENS?
AWS installs Ubuntu OS into VM.

✅ STEP 6 — CHOOSE INSTANCE TYPE
Select:
t2.micro

🎯 WHY?
Because: ✅ free tier ✅ lightweight ✅ sufficient for practicals

✅ STEP 7 — CREATE KEY PAIR
🔥 MOST IMPORTANT STEP
Click:
Create new key pair

ENTER:
Setting	Value
Key Pair Name	KP1
Type	RSA
Format	.pem
CLICK:
Create Key Pair

🎯 WHAT HAPPENS?
AWS downloads:
KP1.pem
This file is used for: ✅ secure SSH login.

⚠️ IMPORTANT
Without .pem file: ❌ cannot connect to VM.

✅ STEP 8 — NETWORK SETTINGS
🔥 VERY IMPORTANT
Allow:
✅ SSH Port:
22

🎯 WHY?
SSH is required for terminal login.

ALSO ENABLE:
✅ HTTP Port:
80
(optional but useful)

✅ STEP 9 — STORAGE SETTINGS
Default:
8 GB
is enough.

🎯 WHAT THIS DOES?
Allocates storage space for VM.

✅ STEP 10 — CLICK “LAUNCH INSTANCE”
AWS now: ✅ creates VM ✅ installs Ubuntu ✅ configures networking ✅ starts machine

🎉 INSTANCE CREATED
You’ll see:
Instance State: Running

✅ STEP 11 — COPY PUBLIC IP
Example:
3.25.153.90

🎯 WHY IMPORTANT?
Used for: ✅ SSH login ✅ SCP transfer

✅ STEP 12 — OPEN TERMINAL
Open Mac terminal.

✅ STEP 13 — GO TO DOWNLOADS FOLDER
Usually PEM file gets downloaded here.
Run:
cd Downloads

✅ STEP 14 — CHECK PEM FILE EXISTS
Run:
ls
Expected:
KP1.pem

✅ STEP 15 — FIX PEM FILE PERMISSIONS
🔥 VERY IMPORTANT
Run:
chmod 400 KP1.pem

🎯 WHY?
AWS blocks insecure private key permissions.
Without this: ❌ SSH fails.

✅ STEP 16 — CONNECT TO EC2 INSTANCE
Run:
ssh -i KP1.pem ubuntu@3.25.153.90
(replace IP with YOUR actual public IP)

🧠 UNDERSTAND THIS COMMAND
Part	Meaning
ssh	Secure Shell
-i KP1.pem	use private key
ubuntu	AWS username
public IP	VM address
⚠️ FIRST TIME CONNECTION
You may see:
Are you sure you want to continue connecting?
Type:
yes

🎉 SUCCESS
Terminal changes from:
apple@MacBookPro
to:
ubuntu@ip-172-31-xx-xx
Meaning: ✅ successfully connected to EC2 VM.

✅ STEP 17 — RUN BASIC LINUX COMMANDS
Check files
ls

Create file
touch test.txt

Verify file
ls
Expected:
test.txt

Update packages
sudo apt update

🎯 WHAT THIS DOES?
Updates Ubuntu package list.

✅ STEP 18 — EXIT VM
Run:
exit

🎉 PRACTICAL COMPLETED
You successfully: ✅ launched EC2 VM ✅ created key pair ✅ configured security group ✅ connected using SSH ✅ executed Linux commands

🔥 IMPORTANT COMMANDS
Command	Purpose
ssh	remote login
chmod 400	secure key permissions
ls	list files
touch	create file
sudo apt update	update packages
🔥 IMPORTANT CONCEPTS
Concept	Meaning
EC2	Virtual Machine service
AMI	Operating System template
Key Pair	Authentication key
SSH	Secure remote terminal
Security Group	Firewall rules
⚠️ COMMON ERRORS + FIXES
Error	Cause	Fix
Permission denied	wrong key	use correct PEM
UNPROTECTED PRIVATE KEY	wrong permissions	chmod 400
Connection timed out	SSH blocked	allow port 22
Host not found	wrong IP	use public IP
